{
  "doc_id": "57375",
  "text": "Previous studies have reported an extremely poor prognosis for pancreatic carcinosarcoma. Shen et al [CITATION_1] reported a carcinosarcoma of the pancreas with liver metastasis combined with a gastrointestinal stromal tumor of the stomach in a 72-year-old female. A radical resection, including a pancreaticoduodenectomy, left hepatic lobe resection and local resection, of the gastric mass was performed, however, the patient succumbed to multiple organ failure at 2 months post-surgery. By contrast, in other cases, survival periods of ≤20 months have been reported [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, 6 months appears to be the most common period for survival [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
